title: Episode #1.1
description: First of a new drama series about the Waterfront Beat of the Liverpool Police. It's the first day for Chief Superintendent Don Henderson. He arrives at work only to find that his new building is not yet built.

title: Episode #1.3
description: PC Ronnie Barker gets his first arrest and leaves Smithey feeling sheepish. CS Don Henderson locks horns with the ACC (Ops) while WDC Jane Long and DS Mike McCarthy hunt sheep rustlers.

title: Episode #1.4
description: The Police Underwater Recovery Team investigate after a motor cruiser is almost hit by bin bags thrown from a bridge; the stolen car racket continues; PC Barkers bike is disappearing bit by bit.

title: Episode #1.5
description: A fraud squad raid hits Fallows and Mike. Don gets media attention while Smithey pays too much attention to Madeline.

title: Episode #1.6
description: Ronnie is injured in the line of duty; Don and June have a dinner date with the Fallows; Mike, Jane and Frank catch a big fish in their net.

title: Episode #1.8
description: Don moves house with June and finds a new home for his division; Ronnie has his first court appearance; Madeline is decoy in the skip murders.

title: Microlights
description: An old crime is given a new twist when armed robbers take to the air.

title: Repossessions
description: Ronnie tries to crack a mortgage mystery.

title: E.P.O.S.
description: An armed robbery takes place at a DIY store where the fraud squad have a surveillance operation running.

title: Pick Up
description: A young girls body is washed up on a beach; WDC Long is volunteered to accompany DS Matthews to Rhodes; PC Barker infiltrates a racist gang.

title: Acid Ship
description: The drugs squad go partying undercover for a raid on an "acid ship" party, but things don't go according to plan; PC Ronnie Barker is finding the pressure too great after infiltrating a gang of right-wing extremists.

title: Dilemma
description: Important breakthrough in the bin-bag murders; DS McVay has a theory about stolen corpses; Ronnie Barker confronts the racists.
